            "body": "Testing current master with vanilla `1.8.3` local server in offline mode inside a Debian machine (client and server):\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n#  cat client_helloworld.js \r\nvar mc = require('minecraft-protocol');\r\n\r\nvar client = mc.createClient({\r\n  host: '127.0.0.1',\r\n  username: 'client001'\r\n});\r\nclient.on('login', function() {\r\n  console.info(\"I'm in!\");\r\n  client.write('chat', { message: 'Pachamama!' });\r\n});\r\nclient.on('chat', function(username, message) {\r\n  console.info('bye bye my friend!');\r\n  client.end('disconnect.quitting');\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nConnection time seems fast to me:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ time node client_helloworld.js \r\nI'm in!\r\nbye bye my friend!\r\n\r\nreal    0m0.302s\r\nuser    0m0.080s\r\nsys     0m0.008s\r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't know. Maybe this only affects Windows, OS X or some specific platform?",
